This paper deals with complexity theory and circuit complexity, which are central topics in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on the class of constant-depth, polynomial-size circuits with majority gates, which falls under the category of circuit complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms, which could fall under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses linear threshold circuits, which are commonly studied in the fields of machine learning and neural networks, making categories such as machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NEUR) also likely.
